1
00:00:14,970 --> 00:00:17,870
Were you born without a brain or something?

2
00:00:18,370 --> 00:00:19,700
It’s two hundred thousand, do you have it?

3
00:00:21,530 --> 00:00:22,730
If you can't find it, don't come back.

4
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,530
I'll get it for you.

5
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:25,870
And this is my business card.

6
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:28,130
In case you change your mind and want to be an actor.

7
00:00:31,970 --> 00:00:33,130
Because back then, I ended up with a stupid partner.

8
00:00:36,570 --> 00:00:38,830
I'm charging you two hundred thousand baht for that cigarette.

9
00:00:41,470 --> 00:00:42,830
If you owe someone, you have to pay them back.

10
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:46,100
When I regained consciousness,

11
00:00:46,770 --> 00:00:49,070
everyone I knew looked at me with fear.

12
00:00:51,300 --> 00:00:53,230
I don't know what happened to me either.

13
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,330
That really wasn't me.

14
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,900
I didn't mean to scare you.

15
00:01:00,970 --> 00:01:01,770
I'm sorry.

16
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:05,269
But I'm scared.

17
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:13,700
Ugh! You’re not feeling it.

18
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,330
Cut the camera!

19
00:01:19,330 --> 00:01:20,130
Why are you talking like that?

20
00:01:21,370 --> 00:01:23,330
I told you to use a high-pitched voice.

21
00:01:23,530 --> 00:01:24,530
So that you sound like the leading female actress.

22
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,200
No way.

23
00:01:29,930 --> 00:01:31,400
What’s with this script? Why is it so damn hard?

24
00:01:32,130 --> 00:01:34,570
Hey. Why? Are you not going to help me?

25
00:01:36,729 --> 00:01:37,530
You're shy, aren't you?

26
00:01:37,930 --> 00:01:38,729
Are you really?

27
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:40,300
What is there to be shy about?

28
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:42,700
Fine, I'll do it myself.

29
00:01:44,970 --> 00:01:47,200
Please don't look at me with those eyes.

30
00:01:48,170 --> 00:01:50,270
It has to be like this. Now you do it.

31
00:01:53,630 --> 00:01:55,070
Please don't look at me with those eyes.

32
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,000
Higher.

33
00:01:58,930 --> 00:01:59,870
Don't look at me...

34
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,000
No way.

35
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:13,400
Happy birthday to you.

36
00:03:14,070 --> 00:03:17,900
Happy birthday to you.

37
00:03:19,100 --> 00:03:23,900
Happy birthday to Angie.

38
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:29,230
Happy birthday to you.

39
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:30,570
Make a wish first, honey.

40
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,530
Yay!

41
00:03:41,270 --> 00:03:41,730
Do you like it, honey?

42
00:03:41,970 --> 00:03:42,670
Yes, I do!

43
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,000
Daddy didn't come alone today.

44
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,530
Surprise!

45
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:01,370
Hello! From today on, I'd like to live here too.

46
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:03,100
Can you name me, please?

47
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,500
Hmm, what should I name you?

48
00:04:07,730 --> 00:04:08,530
How about Candy?

49
00:04:08,970 --> 00:04:11,800
Oh! Candy! What a cute name!

50
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:20,329
From today on, Candy wants to live with P’Angie and P’Pookie also. Please take care of me.

51
00:04:20,470 --> 00:04:22,130
Sure, you have a little sister now.

52
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:30,200
Thank you, Dad.

53
00:04:35,700 --> 00:04:36,330
Let's dig in.

54
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:37,670
Sure.

55
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:38,100
Come here.

56
00:04:39,230 --> 00:04:40,170
Here's a spoon for you.

57
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:42,170
Dad will help pull out the candles.

58
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,200
Alright.

59
00:04:46,230 --> 00:04:47,770
There's even a door here.

60
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,470
There are trees and a bear.

61
00:04:51,070 --> 00:04:52,170
Daddy, do you want to join us?

62
00:04:52,530 --> 00:04:55,370
Hmm. I already ate after work.

63
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:58,330
So this cake is all for Angie.

64
00:05:07,470 --> 00:05:08,270
Is it delicious?

65
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:09,600
It is.

66
00:05:47,130 --> 00:05:48,330
Am I about to get scammed?

67
00:05:52,930 --> 00:05:54,900
Hello. Who is this?

68
00:05:55,300 --> 00:05:56,100
Hello.

69
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,570
You gave me your business card.

70
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:02,700
I want to become an actor.

71
00:06:05,230 --> 00:06:06,500
Oh, yes, yes, yes.

72
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:05,900
Yes? Is there anything I can help you with?

73
00:07:08,270 --> 00:07:09,500
I'm here to see Khajorn.

74
00:07:11,670 --> 00:07:13,000
Oh, just a moment, please.

75
00:07:16,130 --> 00:07:17,630
P'Khajorn, someone is here to see you.

76
00:07:22,570 --> 00:07:25,330
Hey! I thought you wouldn't be able to find the way here.

77
00:07:36,270 --> 00:07:38,230
I'm so glad you contacted me.

78
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:40,870
Come inside.

79
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,300
Come on, come in here.

80
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,970
Sky, go get some water for him, quick.

81
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,230
Alright.

82
00:08:22,170 --> 00:08:23,370
What should I call you?

83
00:08:27,730 --> 00:08:28,530
Sun.

84
00:08:34,530 --> 00:08:36,669
Okay. Sun, it is.

85
00:08:38,169 --> 00:08:38,970
Here’s some water.

86
00:08:41,429 --> 00:08:46,000
Actually, we've met once before. But this time, let me formally introduce myself again.

87
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:47,030
I’m Khajorn.

88
00:08:47,830 --> 00:08:50,070
I’m a talent manager at Dream Entertainment.

89
00:08:51,430 --> 00:08:53,170
And right now, I'm also taking care of Sky.

90
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:02,000
Why did you scout me that day?

91
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:06,230
Because my senses told me to do so.

92
00:09:08,030 --> 00:09:10,470
From the first time I saw you, I knew that

93
00:09:11,470 --> 00:09:13,400
you have potential.

94
00:09:14,970 --> 00:09:17,800
Even though you may look a bit ordinary.

95
00:09:19,570 --> 00:09:21,970
But your eyes are interesting.

96
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:25,900
My eyes?

97
00:09:27,530 --> 00:09:31,930
I mean, you have a character that I can mold.

98
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,230
How about that actor?

99
00:09:46,100 --> 00:09:47,600
Are you talking about P'Sunny?

100
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:54,000
P'Khajorn also takes care of another actor.

101
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:56,870
His name is Sunny.

102
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,470
Used to. I mean, I only used to take care of him.

103
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:05,400
At the moment, Sunny is being taken care of by a new team.

104
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,900
So I have to find some new people on my team as well.

105
00:10:12,770 --> 00:10:14,870
Otherwise, I won't be able to survive here either.

106
00:10:17,600 --> 00:10:18,400
So…

107
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,700
Do you really want to be an actor?

108
00:10:32,930 --> 00:10:34,970
Then take off your hat and let me see.

109
00:10:58,370 --> 00:10:59,770
I agree, very interesting.

110
00:11:00,900 --> 00:11:03,030
Do you think I can be more famous than Sunny?

111
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:10,100
Whoa, but he’s Sunny, you know.

112
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,870
He's like mega famous right now.

113
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,830
There's almost no one who doesn't know him.

114
00:11:13,870 --> 00:11:14,670
I don't know him.

115
00:11:17,830 --> 00:11:18,930
The person I knew

116
00:11:20,130 --> 00:11:21,570
his name is Bank Thanapat.

117
00:11:23,730 --> 00:11:26,530
So you know Sunny's old name?

118
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:31,800
Yes.

119
00:12:00,170 --> 00:12:01,300
See ye! See you later.

120
00:12:15,370 --> 00:12:16,900
People who can consider betraying someone,

121
00:12:20,670 --> 00:12:21,800
they’ll do it eventually.

122
00:12:26,170 --> 00:12:28,270
Have you guys had history together before?

123
00:12:33,330 --> 00:12:35,230
I'm here for revenge.

124
00:12:40,330 --> 00:12:41,330
Revenge?

125
00:13:04,030 --> 00:13:05,130
If it's for that reason,

126
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,370
I think…

127
00:13:09,530 --> 00:13:12,270
I'll have to reconsider whether I can work with you or not.

128
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:23,830
Come in.

129
00:13:34,900 --> 00:13:36,500
Jae Air has confirmed that

130
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:40,170
she will start being your manager from tomorrow onwards.

131
00:13:43,730 --> 00:13:45,430
Thank you very much, P'Kongkiat.

132
00:13:46,030 --> 00:13:48,400
I feel very honored to have Jae Air as my manager.

133
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:53,030
Since you're with Jae Air, behave yourself properly.

134
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,870
Everyone in the industry knows Jae Air.

135
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:00,200
If you embarrass yourself even once, then everyone will know.

136
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:03,530
Don't worry.

137
00:14:04,430 --> 00:14:05,430
I’ll definitely behave nicely.

138
00:14:07,730 --> 00:14:11,300
By the way, what are you going to do about Khajorn?

139
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:13,530
Since he scammed so much money out of me.

140
00:14:14,730 --> 00:14:15,470
Aren't you going to fire him?

141
00:14:19,170 --> 00:14:22,470
And do you have any proof that Khajorn has scammed your money?

142
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:27,570
Well, the money that was transferred didn't match the contract.

143
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:30,200
Things like this you can't just talk, you know?

144
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,630
If there is no concrete documentary evidence,

145
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,230
or any solid proof at all.

146
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,330
Then I’m afraid I can't help you with anything.

147
00:14:45,900 --> 00:14:49,070
Then I'll go gather it first.

148
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,230
Although if there's no evidence,

149
00:14:53,230 --> 00:14:56,330
but if only Kajorn didn’t have anyone talented under him.

150
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:59,370
He wouldn’t last here any longer anyway.

151
00:15:03,870 --> 00:15:04,670
I’ll excuse myself.

152
00:15:05,930 --> 00:15:07,030
Oh, and one more thing.

153
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,700
Since I've helped you this much,

154
00:15:12,370 --> 00:15:16,330
don't forget to take care of the sponsor as scheduled tomorrow.

155
00:15:19,830 --> 00:15:20,270
Alright.

156
00:15:29,870 --> 00:15:33,070
Dream Entertainment is holding a trainee audition in three days.

157
00:15:34,630 --> 00:15:37,330
So I want you to understand the script for this casting well.

158
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,970
And memorize the lines accurately.

159
00:15:53,870 --> 00:15:57,900
What happened to your eyebrow?

160
00:16:01,630 --> 00:16:06,170
Anyway, from now on, you are strictly forbidden from having any more scars on your face alright?

161
00:16:09,930 --> 00:16:11,530
100% sweetness Thai tea is ready.

162
00:16:15,770 --> 00:16:16,630
Thank you.

163
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:23,300
I’m sorry but can you add more syrup?

164
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:25,700
Hmm, so it's 120% sweetness, right?

165
00:16:26,570 --> 00:16:27,930
Can I get 150%?

166
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:29,300
Sure thing, N’Sky.

167
00:16:29,670 --> 00:16:30,470
Thank you.

168
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:33,170
Thank you.

169
00:16:34,470 --> 00:16:37,170
Do you want to eat anything, P'Sun? I'll treat you.

170
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:53,530
I came here for revenge.

171
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:04,300
And how about you, what would you like to order?

172
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:13,230
Is there anything that you like? I can recommend one for you?

173
00:17:21,630 --> 00:17:23,200
P'Sun, do you want to try this?

174
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:25,869
It's delicious, super sweet and refreshing.

175
00:17:31,470 --> 00:17:32,270
Wow1

176
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:37,270
Hey, do you want to try it? It's very delicious.

177
00:17:51,430 --> 00:17:52,670
Black coffee, no sugar.

178
00:17:53,870 --> 00:17:54,600
Okay.

179
00:17:55,400 --> 00:17:58,600
Whoa, P'Sun. If you eat like this, you might not have enough energy.

180
00:17:58,900 --> 00:18:01,000
You don't have to call me 'P'.

181
00:18:02,430 --> 00:18:03,330
Just call me Sun is enough.

182
00:18:28,870 --> 00:18:31,830
My mom died three months after starting the second treatment.

183
00:18:35,370 --> 00:18:37,500
The debt I borrowed from Sia Po to treat my mom.

184
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:41,100
Including interest, it's 1,320,000 baht.

185
00:18:51,470 --> 00:18:52,270
Thank you.

186
00:18:52,770 --> 00:18:53,430
Okay.

187
00:18:53,600 --> 00:18:54,400
How much is it?

188
00:18:54,530 --> 00:18:55,700
Yours is 50 baht.

189
00:18:56,630 --> 00:18:57,930
Is mine almost ready?

190
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:58,800
Oh, it's almost done.

191
00:18:59,030 --> 00:18:59,830
Please wait a moment.

192
00:19:01,430 --> 00:19:02,470
The shop is closed, right?

193
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:03,800
Okay, thanks a lot Sun.

194
00:19:07,030 --> 00:19:07,630
Today's wage.

195
00:19:07,670 --> 00:19:08,200
Thank you.

196
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:08,770
That’s okay.

197
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,030
Good luck to you.

198
00:19:18,070 --> 00:19:20,370
I paid it all back two months ago.

199
00:19:21,600 --> 00:19:24,870
Even if the debt is paid off ิีะ the wrongs people did to me still remain.

200
00:19:26,230 --> 00:19:28,000
And if I wait for karma to work,

201
00:19:28,870 --> 00:19:30,170
It probably won't happen in this lifetime.

202
00:19:31,230 --> 00:19:32,030
It's just me,

203
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:34,670
i’ll bring karma to them myself.

204
00:19:35,530 --> 00:19:36,830
Have you found the money to pay yet?

205
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:38,600
Mr. two Baht.

206
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:43,270
What a bloodsucking leech.

207
00:19:44,470 --> 00:19:45,270
Of course, I am

208
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:48,370
I take care of the finances of this company.

209
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,730
How could I make myself suffer a loss?

210
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:05,370
Oh, I know why you came up here.

211
00:20:08,330 --> 00:20:09,730
You want to flatter me.

212
00:20:10,770 --> 00:20:12,300
so that you can become an actor here.

213
00:20:16,170 --> 00:20:17,800
Because you look ordinary.

214
00:20:18,830 --> 00:20:19,870
Nothing outstanding.

215
00:20:21,230 --> 00:20:22,870
Looks like you don’t have much talent either.

216
00:20:25,330 --> 00:20:27,100
The only way you can pass the audition

217
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:29,900
Is by flattering the person in authority.

218
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:37,300
Running away? I asuume that you're a coward or anything.

219
00:20:39,130 --> 00:20:42,130
Unless you're afraid of getting a scar on your face.

220
00:20:47,170 --> 00:20:51,800
From now on, you are strictly forbidden from having any more scars on your face alright?

221
00:21:25,470 --> 00:21:26,830
You have good eye contact.

222
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:28,900
I like them.

223
00:21:30,270 --> 00:21:31,070
What is your name?

224
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:37,070
And why do you approach me?

225
00:21:38,930 --> 00:21:40,130
That day, I was just asking for a cigarette.

226
00:21:41,230 --> 00:21:43,230
How would I know who you were?

227
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:47,200
Do you really not know me?

228
00:21:49,330 --> 00:21:50,130
No.

229
00:21:50,970 --> 00:21:52,370
Who scouted you?

230
00:22:10,570 --> 00:22:13,170
I think we need to talk a bit about why you want to be an actor.

231
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,170
If you say you want to be an actor for revenge,

232
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:20,770
I think with this mindset it will cause problems at work.

233
00:22:24,530 --> 00:22:25,000
Hello?

234
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,230
Get through the audition alright?

235
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:38,900
And I will reduce the cigarette fee.

236
00:22:43,470 --> 00:22:45,230
And why do I have to do that?

237
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:57,830
How about this?

238
00:22:59,470 --> 00:23:00,870
I'll be your backer.

239
00:23:01,430 --> 00:23:02,400
So that you can become an actor.

240
00:23:04,830 --> 00:23:06,970
Then you can get your revenge for whatever issues it is.

241
00:23:13,470 --> 00:23:14,170
Don’t stick your nose in.

242
00:24:05,070 --> 00:24:09,200
Oh my god!!!

243
00:24:11,970 --> 00:24:13,730
What happened to your face?

244
00:24:17,100 --> 00:24:18,270
I met a crazy person.

245
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:22,170
Sky, go get a cold compress.

246
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,400
Okay.

247
00:24:27,730 --> 00:24:28,530
Bro?

248
00:24:29,370 --> 00:24:30,170
Yeah?

249
00:24:31,870 --> 00:24:34,270
Do you happen to know a very tall guy?

250
00:24:35,370 --> 00:24:40,400
He works here in the department related to finance or something?

251
00:24:41,930 --> 00:24:43,600
You mean like the accounting department?

252
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:49,730
Well, as far as I know, there aren't many men there.

253
00:24:52,270 --> 00:24:54,200
Actually, I don't really mingle with them much.

254
00:24:55,870 --> 00:24:56,670
What’s wrong?

255
00:24:59,870 --> 00:25:01,670
No, it's nothing.

256
00:25:05,330 --> 00:25:07,170
In the meantime, you need to apply the cold compress first.

257
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:09,700
And rehearse your lines with Sky for now.

258
00:25:10,430 --> 00:25:12,870
If you're having any issue then let Sky help you out, alright.

259
00:25:16,170 --> 00:25:20,130
Most importantly, remember that if you ever forget your lines, don't freeze.

260
00:25:22,370 --> 00:25:24,330
Just be yourself as much as possible.

261
00:25:26,870 --> 00:25:28,000
Do you understand what I said?

262
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:29,930
I don't understand you at all.

263
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:32,230
I've been good to you all this time.

264
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:35,070
Why are you doing this to me?

265
00:25:38,530 --> 00:25:40,400
I never truly loved you.

266
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,900
So I’ve had to put up with you all this time.

267
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:57,130
P’... I mean Khun Sun

268
00:25:57,970 --> 00:25:59,170
How about you try again?

269
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:02,400
You need to interpret how the character feels first.

270
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,930
But it's not written in here.

271
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,000
Usually, it doesn’t need to be written down.

272
00:26:10,300 --> 00:26:11,600
Although we are actors,

273
00:26:11,670 --> 00:26:13,430
we have to learn to interpret it ourselves.

274
00:26:16,200 --> 00:26:17,070
That’s hard.

275
00:26:19,570 --> 00:26:20,630
Keep fighting.

276
00:26:21,870 --> 00:26:23,470
You are much better than me.

277
00:26:26,630 --> 00:26:27,670
You call this better?

278
00:26:28,870 --> 00:26:32,270
Well, I get nervous when I'm in front of the camera.

279
00:26:33,130 --> 00:26:34,600
So I can only do stage plays.

280
00:26:36,800 --> 00:26:38,530
I think you can get more jobs.

281
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:40,870
In the future, you'll probably help P'Khajorn out more.

282
00:26:45,770 --> 00:26:47,070
Shall we go again?

283
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:52,330
But let's do some relaxation exercises first. It might help you.

284
00:26:53,070 --> 00:26:53,870
Do it like me.

285
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:56,030
Breathe in and clench your fists.

286
00:26:57,500 --> 00:26:59,230
Then breathe out and open your hands.

287
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,000
How are you going back, Khun Sun?

288
00:27:12,070 --> 00:27:13,100
I’m taking the bus.

289
00:27:14,230 --> 00:27:16,430
Okay, then I'll take a motorcycle taxi.

290
00:27:25,100 --> 00:27:28,570
Wow, he even bought the same car model as P'Penneung?

291
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:32,870
Penneung?

292
00:27:34,730 --> 00:27:35,430
P'Penneung, you don’t know him.

293
00:27:35,670 --> 00:27:36,930
He’s like the top male lead from Dream’s.

294
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:38,430
Haven't you heard of his name before?

295
00:27:43,370 --> 00:27:45,370
P'Sunny has always been like this.

296
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:49,270
He likes to imitate more famous people and replace them with himself.

297
00:27:49,330 --> 00:27:54,070
It means this time, P'Sunny really wants to climb up and replace P'Penneung as the top star.

298
00:28:07,330 --> 00:28:08,530
When I regained my consciousness,

299
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:11,370
Everyone I knew looked at me with fear.

300
00:28:13,830 --> 00:28:15,730
I don't know what happened to me either.

301
00:28:17,330 --> 00:28:18,630
That really wasn't me.

302
00:28:21,070 --> 00:28:22,670
I didn't mean to scare you.

303
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:24,300
I'm sorry.

304
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:27,670
But I'm scared.

305
00:28:29,100 --> 00:28:29,670
Ugh! You’re not feeling it.

306
00:28:31,770 --> 00:28:32,630
Cut the camera!

307
00:28:36,770 --> 00:28:37,570
Why are you talking like that?

308
00:28:38,630 --> 00:28:40,570
Like I told you, use a high-pitched voice.

309
00:28:40,700 --> 00:28:41,700
So that you sound more like the leading female actress.

310
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:45,500
No way.

311
00:29:03,730 --> 00:29:05,570
It's funny that you call me a kid, uncle.

312
00:29:06,330 --> 00:29:08,000
It's funny that you call me a kid, uncle.

313
00:29:08,930 --> 00:29:10,430
It's funny that you call me a kid, uncle.

314
00:29:11,970 --> 00:29:13,830
That's what you, uncle...

315
00:29:17,330 --> 00:29:19,100
Oh, please come in.

316
00:29:20,970 --> 00:29:21,770
Yes.

317
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:24,530
It's funny that you call me a kid, uncle.

318
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:27,000
That's also what I...

319
00:29:31,070 --> 00:29:33,400
Here, I'll put some concealer on your bruise.

320
00:29:35,930 --> 00:29:36,770
It's fine.

321
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:38,670
No way.

322
00:29:39,330 --> 00:29:42,100
Don't you know that if the judges see your face in this condition,

323
00:29:42,170 --> 00:29:42,930
I guarantee that...

324
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:43,830
I believe..

325
00:29:46,530 --> 00:29:47,330
I believe that I can do it.

326
00:29:54,830 --> 00:29:56,830
Anyway, I'll have the team contact you back.

327
00:29:56,900 --> 00:29:57,130
Yes.

328
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,030
Good luck to you.

329
00:29:58,300 --> 00:29:59,100
Thank you.

330
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:03,900
He's quite good.

331
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:04,630
Agreed.

332
00:30:04,670 --> 00:30:05,100
Very nicely done.

333
00:30:05,230 --> 00:30:05,530
Right?

334
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:06,000
I like him.

335
00:30:06,030 --> 00:30:07,300
- His character is clear.
- Yeah.

336
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:09,670
Next in line is Sun, please come in.

337
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:11,670
I agree. Fully agree.

338
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:14,170
He's great. With a bit more grooming, he'll be fine.

339
00:30:22,930 --> 00:30:24,030
A little bit to the center, please.

340
00:30:28,770 --> 00:30:29,470
Hello there.

341
00:30:30,030 --> 00:30:33,300
How about you look at the camera and introduce yourself.

342
00:30:36,070 --> 00:30:38,670
I’m Theemekha Rungsubdee.

343
00:30:40,130 --> 00:30:41,170
My nickname is Sun.

344
00:30:42,770 --> 00:30:43,770
I'm 25 years old.

345
00:30:43,900 --> 00:30:45,700
Hold on. Just a second.

346
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:52,600
Could you tilt your face a bit?

347
00:30:55,570 --> 00:30:58,300
If you can't even take care of your own face,

348
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,530
I think you are not fit to be an actor.

349
00:31:02,470 --> 00:31:03,400
Call in the next person.

350
00:31:07,470 --> 00:31:08,270
Please leave.

351
00:31:08,430 --> 00:31:11,300
Since he's already here, why don't we let him try out a bit?

352
00:31:16,800 --> 00:31:17,600
Go ahead.

353
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:30,330
What are you standing there for? Start acting.

354
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:32,930
The script was sent to you to memorize in advance, wasn't it?

355
00:31:40,630 --> 00:31:41,430
What do you want to do?

356
00:31:43,970 --> 00:31:47,430
If you're not ready to be an actor, I think you'd better go back.

357
00:31:47,530 --> 00:31:49,970
Let’s not waste anyone’s time here.

358
00:31:50,770 --> 00:31:51,330
Get out.

359
00:31:54,030 --> 00:31:56,030
Just be yourself as much as possible.

360
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:05,430
Who said I came here because I want to be an actor?

361
00:32:23,970 --> 00:32:26,630
I came here for my revenge.

362
00:32:39,830 --> 00:32:43,130
Are you threatening me?

363
00:32:44,700 --> 00:32:45,700
You call this a threat?

364
00:32:46,930 --> 00:32:50,800
I’ll show you. What a real threat looks like.

365
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:06,670
Next time when you get a package at your house,

366
00:33:07,730 --> 00:33:09,170
you better watch yourself.

367
00:33:11,270 --> 00:33:18,300
Because I'll be the one delivering it to you by my very own hand.

368
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:26,800
Sun!

369
00:33:31,630 --> 00:33:32,170
Let go of me.

370
00:33:46,700 --> 00:33:51,000
Just seconds ago, I felt like it wasn't me at all.

371
00:33:56,300 --> 00:33:57,400
When I get angry,

372
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:01,800
It's like my soul leaves my body.

373
00:34:04,300 --> 00:34:05,870
Ready to be possessed by anything.

374
00:34:10,370 --> 00:34:11,429
This script is …

375
00:34:14,429 --> 00:34:16,000
I don't know what happened to me either.

376
00:34:18,100 --> 00:34:19,469
That really wasn't me.

377
00:34:21,670 --> 00:34:22,969
I didn't mean to scare you.

378
00:34:24,070 --> 00:34:24,870
I'm sorry.

379
00:34:28,630 --> 00:34:30,400
Please don't look at me with those eyes again.

380
00:34:33,270 --> 00:34:35,699
It's a dialogue from the drama series "Sap Rak".

381
00:34:35,900 --> 00:34:38,570
The character played by Sunny Thanapat.

382
00:34:44,670 --> 00:34:48,969
Wait, was that acting all along?

383
00:34:49,370 --> 00:34:52,300
Oh, yes. It's like method acting.

384
00:34:52,699 --> 00:34:53,500
I'm not okay with this.

385
00:34:55,830 --> 00:34:59,030
He came to cast but didn't act according to the casting script.

386
00:35:00,130 --> 00:35:02,400
And he improvised out of nowhere.

387
00:35:02,600 --> 00:35:04,730
Without telling us beforehand, is that okay?

388
00:35:08,270 --> 00:35:10,500
Exactly. If we choose this kid, doesn’t it mean that we have lowered our standard.

389
00:35:10,570 --> 00:35:13,300
Is he just going to play whatever he wants?

390
00:35:14,830 --> 00:35:16,770
But the way he acted is hard to come by.

391
00:35:17,200 --> 00:35:18,870
Bringing out his own rawness to use.

392
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:20,300
He can definitely go far with this.

393
00:35:21,830 --> 00:35:23,930
But do you understand we are casting?

394
00:35:23,970 --> 00:35:25,670
And the actor doesn't follow the script.

395
00:35:25,770 --> 00:35:27,370
The script is there to guide the actors.

396
00:35:27,770 --> 00:35:28,430
Then what script...

397
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:31,330
How can you talk like this? This is unacceptable, isn't it?

398
00:35:36,230 --> 00:35:37,070
Hello.

399
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:39,730
Yes.

400
00:35:42,800 --> 00:35:45,300
Alright, I'll take care of it.

401
00:35:47,170 --> 00:35:47,970
Yes.

402
00:36:05,700 --> 00:36:11,470
Alright, we'll give this kid a three-month probation.

403
00:36:15,070 --> 00:36:18,500
After that, we'll evaluate again whether to sign a contract or not.

404
00:36:19,770 --> 00:36:20,300
Really?

405
00:36:20,330 --> 00:36:23,000
But if within three months,

406
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:26,900
there is no development whatsoever.

407
00:36:28,070 --> 00:36:29,370
Then there won't be any second chance.

408
00:36:32,170 --> 00:36:32,670
Okay?

409
00:36:34,970 --> 00:36:36,000
Okay.

410
00:36:39,570 --> 00:36:42,530
I’m glad that everything was just an act.

411
00:36:43,070 --> 00:36:48,470
Not everything. Delivering the package part is real.

412
00:37:00,630 --> 00:37:01,930
We prepared this.

413
00:37:04,230 --> 00:37:05,730
You prepared very well.

414
00:37:07,870 --> 00:37:08,800
Awesome right?

415
00:37:09,630 --> 00:37:10,830
Very good.

416
00:37:23,300 --> 00:37:29,500
Welcome Sun Theemekha to the Dream Entertaiment.

417
00:37:34,730 --> 00:37:37,330
Do you know who called the judge?

418
00:37:39,770 --> 00:37:41,770
I don't know, why?

419
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:46,700
I feel like the reason that I passed the audition,

420
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:49,070
was because of that person who called.

421
00:37:50,830 --> 00:37:53,130
It doesn't matter at all.

422
00:37:53,670 --> 00:37:55,400
Right now, what you need to focus on is that

423
00:37:55,430 --> 00:37:57,670
you've been given a three-month chance to prove yourself.

424
00:37:58,670 --> 00:38:01,130
So do your best.

425
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:10,670
Whoa P'Khajorn, don't stress Khun Sun out just yet.

426
00:38:11,730 --> 00:38:14,070
Let's think about what we're going to eat tonight.

427
00:38:14,730 --> 00:38:15,430
Let's go celebrate!

428
00:38:19,270 --> 00:38:20,400
How about Som Tum?

429
00:38:21,700 --> 00:38:22,530
Or Mala?

430
00:38:22,930 --> 00:38:25,800
No more Mala, you eat it all year round.

431
00:38:26,330 --> 00:38:27,130
Let's go.

432
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:28,400
Oh, I forgot my bag.

433
00:38:28,700 --> 00:38:29,500
Let's go.

434
00:38:30,430 --> 00:38:31,830
I think I'm bored of Som Tum.

435
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:34,000
Oh, how many times have I taken you to eat Mala?

436
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:35,000
We eat it only like every week.

437
00:38:35,130 --> 00:38:39,370
- Someday when you have a stable job and make money then you can treat me to Mala. Although today I'm paying and I want to eat Som Tum.
- Let's go, Khun Sun.

438
00:38:39,770 --> 00:38:40,570
Understood?

439
00:38:40,630 --> 00:38:43,030
All you eat is Som Tum.

440
00:38:43,370 --> 00:38:45,400
Oh wow, it's Khajorn.

441
00:38:48,270 --> 00:38:49,230
I’m surprised that you haven't been fired yet.

442
00:38:51,470 --> 00:38:52,700
A scammed manager.

443
00:38:58,300 --> 00:38:59,870
Wait, let me explain more to you first.

444
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:04,570
The reason I didn't accept that sponsor job you wanted.

445
00:39:06,130 --> 00:39:07,670
Because it's a grey business.

446
00:39:08,400 --> 00:39:09,570
How was I scamming you?

447
00:39:10,430 --> 00:39:11,970
That wasn’t just the reason alright?

448
00:39:13,070 --> 00:39:14,030
I already told you, didn't I?

449
00:39:15,900 --> 00:39:18,000
It’s because you're such a terrible manager.

450
00:39:21,270 --> 00:39:23,230
Now you're left with actors who can't be used.

451
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:27,700
Soon, the company president won't keep you.

452
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:29,300
You’re so useless.

453
00:39:34,530 --> 00:39:36,530
But right now, P'Khajorn has got someone new to take care of.

454
00:39:38,530 --> 00:39:40,000
I'm telling you, this guy is godlike.

455
00:39:42,370 --> 00:39:43,630
This was just his first audition.

456
00:39:44,100 --> 00:39:45,030
And he already passed.

457
00:39:46,430 --> 00:39:48,930
Even when P'Boss was watching the new kid, he was shaking nonstop.

458
00:39:51,170 --> 00:39:52,030
Someone like P'Sunny,

459
00:39:54,730 --> 00:39:55,900
get ready to be thrown in the trash.

460
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:56,970
Hey, that's enough.

461
00:39:59,270 --> 00:40:00,070
Who the hell is he?

462
00:40:04,630 --> 00:40:05,430
Let's go.

463
00:40:06,870 --> 00:40:07,770
If you want to go.

464
00:40:08,600 --> 00:40:09,400
Well, actually no,

465
00:40:10,700 --> 00:40:12,270
You never wanted to go with us anyway.

466
00:40:17,170 --> 00:40:18,130
Suit yourself then.

467
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:36,700
I need to use the restroom first.

468
00:40:37,570 --> 00:40:38,870
Once you're done, we’ll see you in the car.

469
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:49,200
Hello.

470
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:52,570
I have something I want to ask.

471
00:40:57,570 --> 00:40:59,530
That new kid of Khajorn who just passed the audition.

472
00:41:00,300 --> 00:41:01,100
Who the hell is he?

473
00:41:04,270 --> 00:41:05,500
If you don't know, go find out.

474
00:41:06,830 --> 00:41:08,070
Go find a way to get rid of him.

475
00:41:09,470 --> 00:41:10,700
Whatever you do is your business.

476
00:41:12,500 --> 00:41:13,430
Just make it so he can't stay here.

477
00:41:20,730 --> 00:41:21,230
That's all for now.

478
00:41:31,300 --> 00:41:32,100
Who’s there?

479
00:41:40,030 --> 00:41:40,930
I’m asking who?

480
00:42:08,070 --> 00:42:09,530
People are talking all over the building.

481
00:42:10,500 --> 00:42:12,300
About you bringing a knife to the audition.

482
00:42:13,100 --> 00:42:15,270
To both of P'Khajorn's superstars.

483
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:17,270
Bottoms up.

484
00:42:20,030 --> 00:42:22,400
Calling all photographers to an event, really?

485
00:42:23,370 --> 00:42:24,630
So what do you want?

486
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:27,970
In this industry, which photographer is the best?

487
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:29,630
Who are you guys?

488
00:42:31,430 --> 00:42:34,070
How can you be so sure that you’ll survive in this industry?

489
00:43:07,600 --> 00:43:09,270
I have no idea who it's for.

